Question: Why is it that most long distance relationships are unsuccessful ?
Answer:
That’s the million dollar question right here.
  
  I think most long distance relationships don’t work out due to trust and communication. I mean it’s very important to build trust with the person you’re in a relationship with long distance but it can be hard because you never know what they can be doing. Trust is so important to have when you’re in a relationship and if you don’t have that then there’s really no relationship between the two of you. I mean it takes time to build trust by not only their words but also their actions and if they show you, you can trust them then you’ll start to slowly be able to trust that person and not have to worry about them doing other things behind your back. But then on the other hand if they show you, you can’t trust them due to their actions and how they present themselves to you that’s a whole different story. But one factor in to why long distance relationships don’t work out is trust. You gotta have trust with the other person and slowly build it.
  
  The other factor would definitely be communication. I mean obviously if it’s long distance there’s going to be different time zones like you might be 3 hours behind and the person you’re with might be 3 hours ahead of you but that doesn’t mean anything if they really like you, they will communicate with you and talk to you and find the time to do so. No one is ever to “busy” to communicate with someone they really want and like. No matter how busy someone is they will find the time to communicate with you. People are busy but if they like you, they’ll call or text you. We make time for what we want. Communication is always key because if you don’t communicate with one another the partner can start to overthink and start to worry and you never want that, it’s not healthy. It’s important to always find the time to message one another no matter what. Keeping the communication alive is what is important in long distance relationships even in any relationship.
  
  Also another factor can be physical and showing affection. Obviously if you’re in a long distance relationship you can’t touch one another or show affection. That would be very difficult to do. Many people love holding hands, cuddling, kissing, sleeping next to each other, hugging, etc. And in long distance relationships you can’t do that so you can only really use your words to say what you would like to do with one another when you meet. That’s also why long distance relationships don’t work out. It’s craving one another’s touch and feeling that affection.
  
  I mean don’t get me wrong there’s many long distance relationships that do work out because they’re able to trust one another and communicate and plus build that strong emotional connection and feel those positive vibes off of one another. That strong connection that you can build with someone in a long distance relationship is quite amazing. Just being able to feel how strong of a connection you two have emotionally and mentally is always great.
